protocol.description:
Evaluation_Test_Type: Interval: At Absolute Minimum
Forecast_Test_Type: EvaluationNot recommended: series complete
General_Description: This test case describes when an adolescent child is administered a third dose of the HPV vaccine at 16 weeks minus 1 day after the first dose that the dose is considered to be valid.  The series is complete. (Prior to 12/16/16, 16 weeks - 4 days was allowed to be used as an Absolute Minimum Interval from Target Dose #1).
